## Environment Variables

Create a `.env.local` file in the project root. **Never commit this file.**

```bash
# .env.local

# --- Public variables (exposed to the browser) ---
# Prefix with NEXT_PUBLIC_ to expose to the client bundle.
NEXT_PUBLIC_API_URL=http://localhost:4000
NEXT_PUBLIC_APP_URL=http://localhost:3000
{% if use_auth and auth_provider == "clerk" %}
NEXT_PUBLIC_CLERK_PUBLISHABLE_KEY=pk_test_...
{% endif %}

# --- Server-only variables (never exposed to the browser) ---
{% if use_auth and auth_provider == "next-auth" %}
NEXTAUTH_URL=http://localhost:3000
NEXTAUTH_SECRET=generate-with-openssl-rand-base64-32
{% elif use_auth and auth_provider == "clerk" %}
CLERK_SECRET_KEY=sk_test_...
{% elif use_auth and auth_provider == "custom-jwt" %}
JWT_SECRET=generate-with-openssl-rand-base64-32
JWT_EXPIRY=1h
REFRESH_TOKEN_EXPIRY=7d
{% endif %}
```

> **Rule:** `NEXT_PUBLIC_` variables are bundled into the client JavaScript. Never put secrets, API keys, or tokens in `NEXT_PUBLIC_` variables.

